    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.21"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>
                </figure>
                    <hi rend="caps">THE KANSAS CITY STAR</hi> 
                        <lb/>
                        The Kansas City Times 
                            <lb/>
                        (<hi rend="caps">THE</hi> <hi rend="italics">Morning</hi> <hi rend="caps">KANSAS CITY STAR</hi>) 
                            <lb/>
                    1729 Grand Avenue ∙ Kansas City, Missouri 64108 ∙ [816] 421-1200 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 18, 1971</dateline> 
                
                    <salute>Esteemed Friend John Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My heart sinks with embarrassment to learn belatedly about the festivities in Nebraska last month. My attendance was impossible because I was recovering from eye surgery. But I would have participated with a "Greeting" had I known.</p> 
                
                <p>Alas, notif<add>i</add>cation arrived at the time I was an emergency case, and a letter from your friends was mislaid among other items put aside for later attention.</p>
                
                <p>Arriving in the meantime were your kindly inscribed volumes of "Mountain Men" and "Twilight of the Siou<del>s</del><add>x</add>." These I shal<add>l</add> treasure always--but they will sadden me also with the memory that I did not participate in the "John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt Day."</p> 
                
                <p>Stay with us dear <del>firned</del><add>friend</add>, I want want to be with you next time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Warm regards,</salute> 
                
                    <signed>Thorpe Menn</signed> 
                    <signed>Thorpe Menn,
                    Literary Editor</signed> 
                </closer>
                
                <note>Ansd 
                    9-3-71</note>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">PS &#8212;</hi></opener> <p>I enclose a copy for Carroll Thompson, whose letter does not include an address</p>
                    <closer>
                        <salute>cheers</salute> 
                        <signed>TM</signed>
                    </closer>
                </postscript>
                
                (no over) 
